title.narrative: Effective and efficient management of the Child Protection Programme

description.narrative: Despite the prolonged challenges of COVID-19, UNICEF continued to provide its support to the Government and partners to implement the rolling work plan and deliver child protection outcomes in 2021. The focus was on strengthening the child protection system, social service workforce development, and COVID-19 preparedness and response. Fundraising for the child protection sector remains challenging. The CO developed the CPD 2022-2026 and the child protection programme strategy note, engaging numerous partners across the social welfare, justice, education, and health sectors from the national and sub-national government and CSOs. | Status:Met | As-of Date:16/12/2021
